<TITLE> Foggy, cold spell to last few days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com)  Moderate to dense fog that has covered southern, central, and western regions of the country will continue for the next few days, the met office said on Tuesday. Sakedul Alam of the Meteorological Department told bdnews24.com: "Fog is lasting in the regions from late night to morning and temperatures are falling." Temperatures of 13.8 and 28.8 degrees Celsius were recorded respectively as the lowest and highest in Rajshahi and Cox's Bazar on Tuesday. Temperatures 16.5 and 22.4 degrees Celsius were registered respectively as the lowest and highest in the capital. The met office said in a 24-hour advance forecast that weather may remain dry accompanied by partly cloudy skies. Moderate to thick fog looks likely to continue in the southern, central, and western regions and the river basins. Light to moderate fog may fall elsewhere in the country and overnight temperatures will remain unchanged. bdnew
